reviewText: Very good quailty I have most of these movies
Returned item. Item was in wrong/different packaging/cover. Something like that can definitely confuse customers. Just because of that, made me think that it wasn't the movie that I've anticipated
One of my favorite teenage movie memories! Especially with the original Ocean dubbed voice actors by Pioneer Entertainment.

Earlier movies aren't as good as the older ones, but Turles is one of the often forgotten villians. I wish there was more character backstory, but what can you do?
Must see.

i received the package and found the item was falsely described, it is not the original dub from 1999-2000 with the original english cast, it is the 2006 version which is subpar in comparison. i will be returning and want a full refund. waste of time!
Product received as advertised would do business with seller again, Thanks
Dbz is a great action movie.  Eating the fruit from the tree gives u power 3 or 10 times your strength.  A must see for fans

A note of caution, the product listed is not the one being sold. The cover art shown is for the original Pioneer release with the Ocean House Dub. However, the product being sold is the later Funimation Dub. Thankfully, my seller refunded my purchase, but be careful. Great movie either way, I just prefer the original dub.

This movie is pretty good. The story and the action in this movie is pretty cool. Also the villains in this movie are pretty cool especially Turles. Turles is so evil and his fighting is just cool. Lots of cool fights in this movie, Goku vs Daiz, Yamcha vs Armond, Tien and Chaiotzu vs Raisin and Lakasei, Gohan vs one of the twins. Goku vs Turles is by far one of the best fights with Goku in it. Definitely check this movie out.

this movie does not have the same actors as funimation so if you are a fan of funimation i recommend that you do not buy this movie. the actors sound totally different than funimation , not even close. The only thing the same is the plot. That is why I gave it a two star not a one star review.
